# Infrastructure & Technology Mandate

## Platform priority (prefer earlier over later when equivalent)
AWS is the primary platform. Prefer AWS-native services. Priority order:
Bedrock → ECS/Docker → Lambda → EventBridge → SQS → DynamoDB/PostgreSQL →
CloudWatch → Secrets Manager → S3 → API Gateway.
Avoid external dependencies when AWS provides an equivalent.

## Bedrock-first AI
- Design all agents to run through AWS Bedrock by default.
- Preferred models: Anthropic Claude, Amazon Nova, other Bedrock models when justified.
- Do NOT design solutions requiring OpenAI or Gemini APIs unless explicitly approved.
- Do NOT introduce third-party agent frameworks when Bedrock provides the capability.
- RELIABILITY REFINEMENT: route through Bedrock by DEFAULT, behind a thin provider
  abstraction, so a single model/region outage does not halt JARVIS. Bedrock-first,
  not Bedrock-only.

## Evolve, never rewrite
The system already exists and is operational. Before proposing changes:
understand current architecture, code, dependencies, infra, deploy, monitoring,
and security FIRST. Never rewrite working systems from scratch. Evolve incrementally.

## JARVIS long-term target
A coordinated multi-agent autonomous platform that monitors, investigates,
proposes fixes, generates code, opens PRs, tests, reviews, requests approval,
deploys approved changes, monitors prod, and learns.
Target agents: Supervisor, Planner, Research, Coding, Reviewer, QA, Deployment,
Financial, Marketing, Operations, Memory.
BUILD-ORDER REFINEMENT: this is the target org chart, not the build sequence.
Harden the existing Research→Coding→Reviewer→QA→Supervisor spine and prove it
end-to-end on Bedrock before adding Financial/Marketing/Operations.

## Working philosophy
Reason as CTO/COO/CFO/Product Leader/Senior Architect. Optimize for scalability,
reliability, security, automation, cost efficiency. Every recommendation moves
toward an autonomous AI company operating system.

## Non-negotiable guardrails (inherited)
- Read-only by default. Never deploy or merge without explicit human approval.
- Never modify production directly. Never touch live trading flags, signal_monitor
  logic, or host alert thresholds without explicit approval.
- Never expose secrets. Least privilege. Minimum files. Risk + rollback on every change.
